                        </a></div></div><ol class="senses_multiple" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" ox5000="y" sensenum="1" id="acid_sng_1" hclass="sense" cefr="b2"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><div class="symbols" hclass="symbols" htag="div"><a href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxford3000-5000?dataset=english&amp;list=ox5000&amp;level=b2"><span class="ox5ksym_b2"> </span></a></div></span><span class="grammar" htag="span" hclass="grammar">[uncountable, countable]</span> <span class="labels" hclass="labels" htag="span">(<span class="subj" subj="chem">chemistry</span>)</span> <span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a chemical, usually a liquid, that contains <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hydrogen" title="hydrogen definition"><span class="ndv">hydrogen</span></a> and has a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/ph" title="pH definition"><span class="ndv">pH</span></a> of less than seven. The <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hydrogen" title="hydrogen definition"><span class="ndv">hydrogen</span></a> can be replaced by a metal to form a salt. <span class="dh">Acids</span> usually have a bitter sharp taste and can often burn holes in or damage things they touch.</span><ul class="examples" htag="ul" hclass="examples"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">The acid burned a hole in her coat.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">Stomach acids can break down the poison.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">You will need a special chemical to neutralize the acid.</span></li></ul> <span class="xrefs" hclass="xrefs" xt="cp" htag="span"><span class="prefix">compare</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/alkali" title="alkali definition"><span class="xr-g" bord="n" dict="all" href="alkali_e"><span class=